snippet.textDisplay:
I have a 2006 trailblazer that was in just as bad of shape when I bought. I worked in a detail shop for years and the only way to get a carpet this bad off clean is to take it out and pressure wash it like you did the floor mats. Yeah it adds a couple days depending on weather but my trailblazer looked and smelled brand new after. You can shampoo all day but if you aren’t removing the seats to get in around those low spots it’s still going to have a lingering smell. Not knocking you in any way just maybe some info for someone doing it themselves. You did what you were paid for and striping it out would have added days to the job.

To be honest if the owner let it get this bad once it’ll be this way again in no time at all. All in all you did a great job

You can shampoo all day but if you aren’t removing the seats to get in around those low spots it’s still going to have a lingering smell. Not knocking you in any way just maybe some info for someone doing it themselves. You did what you were paid for and striping it out would have added days to the job.
